{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
{{ parent() }}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset('css/home.css') }}">
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="jumbotron">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-5 col-xs-12 text-center">
				<img class="img-circle hello-animation"
						 src="{{ asset('img/hello-animation.gif') }}" alt="Me, waving hello">
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-7 col-xs-12">
				<h1>Why, hello.</h1>

				<p>
					Oh, my... you've found me and my virtual home on&nbsp;the&nbsp;internet.
				</p>

				<p>
					This site is ostensibly a website designed as a web based portfolio,
					but it's likely going to devolve into a showcase of
					<a href="catpoo">robot project</a> or time lapse videos of
					mundane scenarios.
				</p>

			</div>
		</div>


	</div>
</div>

<div class="container">
	<section class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-5">
			<header class="section_header row">
				<img class="section_icon" src="{{ asset('img/icons/catpoo.svg') }}">
				<h2 class="section_title">
					Cat Antagonizing Tactical Platform of&nbsp;Oppression
				</h2>
			</header>
		</div>

		<div class="section_description col-xs-12 col-md-7">
			<p>
				Back when I was a young kid, I always wanted to build a robot. I never
				managed to talk my parents into giving me thousands and thousands of
				dollars to fund my research. It was a difficult&nbsp;time.
			</p>

			<p>
				Fast forward 20 years, I have a career and the necessary income. I also
				have cats. The decision was made before I even thought of what to do:
				build a device to terrorize my&nbsp;cats.
			</p>

		</div>

		<div class="section_more-info col-xs-12 col-md-7 col-md-offset-5">
			<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="catpoo" role="button">Learn more</a>
		</div>


	</section>

	<hr>

	<section class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-5">
			<header class="section_header row">
				<img class="section_icon" src="{{ asset('img/icons/resume.svg') }}">
				<h2 class="section_title">R&eacute;sum&eacute;</h2>
			</header>
		</div>

		<div class="section_description col-xs-12 col-md-7">
			<p>
				Whenever someone wants to know something about me, I'm tempted to provide
				this&nbsp;link...
			</p>

			<p>
				Whether you found my page on
				<a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/tim-doerzbacher/86/438/664/"
					 rel="external" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> or
				<a href="#joke" rel="external"
					 data-toggle="popover" data-placement="bottom"
					 title="This was a joke" data-trigger="hover click"
					 data-content="You were expecting a functional link? I'm flattered, but let's keep things professional.">OkCupid</a>,
				we all know this is why you're&nbsp;here.
			</p>

		</div>

		<div class="section_more-info col-xs-12 col-md-7 col-md-offset-5">
			<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="catpoo" role="button">Learn more</a>
		</div>

	</section>

	<hr>

	<section class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-12 col-md-5">
			<header>
				<img class="section_icon" src="{{ asset('img/icons/artwork.svg') }}">
				<h2 class="section_title">Artwork</h2>
			</header>
		</div>

		<div class="section_description col-xs-12 col-md-7">
			<p>
				I went to art school because I wanted to make video games. I wanted to
				do it all from the models or the&nbsp;engine.
			</p>

			<p>
				Now I occasionally make artwork to try to justify the student&nbsp;loan.
			</p>

		</div>

		<div class="section_more-info col-xs-12 col-md-7 col-md-offset-5">
			<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="catpoo" role="button">Learn more</a>
		</div>

	</section>
</div>

{% endblock %}

